 Police Elizabeth on Friday morning arrested a 45-year-old man for allegedly killing his 47-year-old girlfriend at Malcolm Street, in Zwide Township, Port Elizabeth. According to the police, the suspect and the victim were drinking when a fight broke out between them. “The suspect accused the victim of cheating on him and then he stabbed her to death,” said police spokesperson, Constable Mncedisi Mbombo. He added that the deceased sustained serious injuries on the head and chest - she died instantly. The suspect will appear before the New Brighton Magistrate's Court on Monday facing a charge of murder. 